'''Zakaria El Ouahdi''' ({{langx|ary|زكرياء الواحدي}};<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://nichan.ma/302047/|title=أندية أوروبية تتسابق لضم زكرياء الواحدي وسط استعداد "غينك" لرحيله|date=17 May 2025 }}</ref> born 31 December 2001), is a professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[right winger]] or a [[right-back]] for [[Belgian Pro League]] club [[KRC Genk|Genk]]. Born in Belgium, he plays for the [[Morocco national football team|Morocco national team]].

==Early life==
El Ouahdi was born in [[Hoboken]] in the [[Antwerp Province]] in a family of eight children. His parents are of Moroccan descent.<ref>{{cite web|title=Zakaria El Ouahdi, le chouchou du stade Machtens|publisher=La DH Les Sports+|url=https://www.dhnet.be/sports/football/division-1b/rwdm/2022/12/18/zakaria-el-ouahdi-le-chouchou-du-stade-machtens-DBC43FEMEZBQ7N4EPJSDXLUA44/|date=12 December 2022|language=fr}}</ref>

==Club career==
In June 2021, El Ouadhi joined the under-21 side of [[RWDM47|RWD Molenbeek]].<ref>{{cite web|language=nl-BE|title=Twee jaar na zijn komst heeft Zakaria El Ouahdi de titel met RWDM beet: "Nooit gedacht dat het zo snel zou gaan"|url=https://www.nieuwsblad.be/cnt/dmf20230514_94809962|publisher=Het Nieuwsblad |date=14 May 2023}}</ref> After good performances, El Ouadhi was regularly invited to train with the first team, and was awarded his first professional contract on 9 September 2021.<ref>{{cite web|language=fr|title=D1B: Zakaria El Ouahdi signe son premier contrat pro au RWDM|url=https://www.sudinfo.be/art/829913/article/2021-09-09/d1b-zakaria-el-ouahdi-signe-son-premier-contrat-pro-au-rwdm|website=sudinfo.be|date=9 September 2021}}</ref>

On 14 August 2021, he made his professional debut in [[Challenger Pro League]] in RWD Molenbeek's 3–1 victory against [[Royal Excel Mouscron]].{{citation needed|date=July 2025}} On 3 October, he scored his first goal in professional, awarding a 2–1 win for his club against [[KMSK Deinze|Deinze]].{{citation needed|date=July 2025}}

On 12 March 2023, El Ouadhi scored his first career hattrick against [[Club NXT]], offering an important 3–2 win for RWD Molenbeek for their fight for promotion.<ref>{{cite web |title=RWDM vs. Club Brugge II - 12 March 2023 |url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2023/03/12/belgium/second-division/daring-club-de-molenbeek/belgium-club-brugge-kv-ii/4038574/ |website=Soccerway |access-date=14 August 2023}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |language=fr-FR|title=Le RWDM se rapproche de la montée grâce à un triplé de Zakaria El Ouahdi |url=https://bx1.be/categories/news/le-rwdm-se-rapproche-de-la-montee-grace-a-un-triple-de-zakaria-el-ouahdi/ |website=BX1 |date=12 March 2023}}</ref> He terminated the [[2022–23 Challenger Pro League|2022–23]] season by winning the league with RWD Molenbeek and gained a promotion to the [[Belgian Pro League|Jupiler Pro League]].<ref>{{cite web |language=fr |title=Molenbeek, champion de D2 belge, promu en Pro League |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Molenbeek-champion-de-d2-belge-promu-en-pro-league/1396492 |publisher=L'Équipe|date=14 May 2023}}</ref><ref name="d2 champs">{{cite web |language=fr |title=D1B – El Ouahdi aux anges après le sacre du RWDM: "Vivre ces sensations à mon âge, c'est fantastique" |url=https://www.sudinfo.be/id664596/article/2023-05-14/d1b-el-ouahdi-aux-anges-apres-le-sacre-du-rwdm-vivre-ces-sensations-mon-age-cest |website=sudinfo.be |date=14 May 2023}}</ref> El Ouadhi named was as Molenbeek's player of the season and figured in the league's best XI of the season.<ref name="best xi">{{cite web |language=fr |title=D1B - Equipe de l'Année // AILIER DROIT : Zakaria El Ouahdi (RWDM)|url=https://www.proximus.be/pickx/fr/2334927/d1b-equipe-de-lannee-ailier-droit-zakaria-el-ouahdi-rwdm |website=www.proximus.be|access-date=14 August 2023}}</ref>

On 5 September 2023, El Ouahdi signed for [[K.R.C. Genk|Genk]] on an initial three-year deal with the option for a further twelve months.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.krcgenk.be/nl/nieuws/5268/twee-nieuwe-gezichten-arriveren-in-de-cegeka-arena|trans-title=TWO NEW FACES ARRIVE AT THE CEGEKA ARENA|title=TWEE NIEUWE GEZICHTEN ARRIVEREN IN DE CEGEKA ARENA|language=Dutch|website=www.krcgenk.be/nl|date=5 September 2023|accessdate=5 September 2023}}</ref>

==International career==
Holding both Belgian and Moroccan citizenship, El Ouadhi chose to represent [[Morocco national football team|Morocco]] in international level. On 9 June 2023, he was called up by coach Issame Charaï in [[Morocco national under-23 football team|Morocco U-23]] squad for the [[2023 U-23 Africa Cup of Nations]].<ref>{{cite web |language=fr |title=CAN U23: la liste des Lionceaux dévoilée, avec El Khannouss et Ezzalzouli |url=https://sport.le360.ma//maroc/can-u23-la-liste-des-lionceaux-devoilee-avec-el-khannouss-et-ezzalzouli-104477 |website=Le360 Sport |access-date=14 August 2023}}</ref> El Ouadhi appeared in four out of five matches during the tournament, and scored one goal against [[Mali national under-23 football team|Mali U-23]] in the semi-final match.<ref>{{cite web |language=fr-FR|title=CAN U23 : Le Maroc en finale au détriment du Mali et se qualifie pour les JO - La Vie éco |url=https://www.lavieeco.com/au-royaume/can-u23-le-maroc-en-finale-au-detriment-du-mali-et-se-qualifie-pour-les-jo/|website=lavieeco.com|date=5 July 2023}}</ref> Morocco U-23 won the tournament as El Ouadhi figured in the competition's team of the tournament as the best [[Defender (association football)|right-back]].<ref name="MAR U23">{{cite web |language=fr |title=Le Maroc remporte la CAN U23 au bout de la prolongation |url=https://www.sofoot.com/breves/can-u23-le-maroc-detrone-legypte-au-bout-de-la-prolongation |website=SOFOOT.com |date=9 July 2023}}</ref><ref name="can u23 best">{{cite web |language=fr-FR |title=CAN U23: L'équipe type de la compétition dévoilé |url=https://africafootunited.com/can-u23-lequipe-type-de-la-competition-devoile/ |website=Africa Foot United |date=9 July 2023 |access-date=14 August 2023 |archive-date=20 July 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230720161714/https://africafootunited.com/can-u23-lequipe-type-de-la-competition-devoile/ |url-status=dead }}</ref>

El Ouadhi earned his first senior call-up for [[2025 Africa Cup of Nations qualification|2025 Africa Cup of Nations qualifiers]] against [[Gabon national football team|Gabon]] and [[Lesotho national football team|Lesotho]] in September 2024, but remained on the bench for both games.<ref>{{cite web |title=Morocco vs. Gabon - 6 September 2024 - Soccerway |url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2024/09/06/africa/africa-cup-of-nations-qualification/morocco/gabon/4406331/ |website=Soccerway |access-date=18 October 2024}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Lesotho vs. Morocco - 9 September 2024 - Soccerway |url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2024/09/09/africa/africa-cup-of-nations-qualification/lesotho/morocco/4406334/ |website=Soccerway |access-date=18 October 2024}}</ref>

